    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Vegan Pad Thai</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>8 oz rice noodles</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 cup firm tofu, cubed</li>
            <li>1 cup broccoli florets</li>
            <li>1 red bell pepper, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>2 carrots, julienned</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1/4 cup soy sauce</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons maple syrup or agave nectar</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon rice vinegar</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon tamarind paste</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes (optional, for spice)</li>
            <li>1 cup bean sprouts</li>
            <li>1/4 cup chopped peanuts</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro and lime wedges for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Cook the rice noodles according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.</li>
            <li>In a large pan or wok, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add cubed tofu and cook until golden brown on all sides. Remove from the pan and set aside.</li>
            <li>In the same pan, add more oil if needed. Add minced garlic, sliced red bell pepper, julienned carrots, and broccoli florets. Stir-fry until the vegetables are tender-crisp.</li>
            <li>In a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce, maple syrup or agave nectar, rice vinegar, tamarind paste, and red pepper flakes (if using).</li>
            <li>Push the vegetables to one side of the pan and pour the sauce into the pan. Add the cooked rice noodles and tofu. Toss everything together until well coated and heated through.</li>
            <li>Add bean sprouts and toss again for an additional minute.</li>
            <li>Remove from heat and serve the Vegan Pad Thai hot, garnished with chopped peanuts, fresh cilantro, and lime wedges.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Vegan Pad Thai!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

